# Kamal secrets — production
# Lido pelo Kamal como shell script. Valores são puxados do 1Password CLI (`op`).
# Pré-requisito no host de deploy: `op` instalado e autenticado no cofre rota-saude-prod.
# Ver ADR-0011.

OP_VAULT="rota-saude-prod"

require_op() {
  if ! command -v op >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    echo "1Password CLI (op) não está instalado neste host" >&2
    exit 1
  fi
}
require_op

# Registry (GitHub Container Registry).
KAMAL_REGISTRY_PASSWORD=$(op read "op://${OP_VAULT}/ghcr-bot/token")

# Rails master key — descriptografa config/credentials/production.yml.enc.
RAILS_MASTER_KEY=$(op read "op://${OP_VAULT}/rails-master-key/credential")

# Postgres do accessory (host dedicado).
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=$(op read "op://${OP_VAULT}/postgres/password")
DATABASE_URL="postgres://rota_saude:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@db.rota-saude.example:5432/rota_saude_production?sslmode=require"

# WhatsApp Cloud API — tokens de produção.
WHATSAPP_VERIFY_TOKEN=$(op read "op://${OP_VAULT}/whatsapp/verify_token")
WHATSAPP_APP_SECRET=$(op read "op://${OP_VAULT}/whatsapp/app_secret")
WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN=$(op read "op://${OP_VAULT}/whatsapp/access_token")
